Exam Mode: Exam Type: Objective type (MCQs) Total no. of questions: 150 Marking Scheme: 1 mark for each correct answer Negative Marking: There will be no negative marking Exam Duration: 2.30 hours Exam Time: 10:00 am to 03:30 pm Telangana Teacher Eligibility Test is one of the prestigious teaching examination of the state Telangana. Each year, several candidates appear for this exam, and only a few candidates are able to qualify the exam. It will be helpful for those candidates who are appearing for the exam to refer to the preparation strategies of TET qualified candidates. Customize their strategies as per the requirement and start the preparation of the exam. Time management during the preparation of STET exam is crucial. It is necessary to manage time between studying and revision. Each section of syllabus must get enough time to practise. Also, it becomes vital to revise topics with previous year papers to keep them fresh in mind. Along with hard work, smart work is also crucial for the STET preparation. It becomes necessary to identify the important topics for the exam. Practise STET previous year question papers and note down the important topics and frequently asked questions of the exam. Candidates can also start their preparation with these important section and questions. Before filling the application form, candidates must keep the following things ready: Receipt of payment Scanned or digital photograph Scanned signature of the candidate Working e-mail and mobile number Application Fee Candidates have to pay Rs.400/- as application fee. Application fee can only be submitted online. Candidates who are fulfilling the Eligibility Criteria set by officials will be able to sit for the Exam, others will be rejected at the time of scrutiny of documents.
